    "course_title": "DISTURBANCE ECOLOGY LAB (I): HERBIVORES AND FIRE",
    "description": "Explores natural and anthropogenic disturbances occurring in forest ecosystems through hands on learning experiences. Emphasis on the role of herbivores and fire with examination of management strategies. Applies basic ecological laboratory and field techniques to understanding disturbances that change the physical environment and disrupt ecosystem structure.",
